<br />
<br />I have a question about the (contest) legality of accessing char-rom.  I want to implement pixel-perfect collision detection in my game.  To do this the NES CPU needs access to the pixel placement in some of my sprites.  Am I allowed to convert some of my sprites in char-rom to bit patterns in system ram (say to $0300)?
<br />
<br />If not then fine.  I'll just have to store the data twice, once in char-rom and once in prog-rom.  It just seems weird to duplicate data...

		

